    "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nWhen `tl.disable_warp_specialized=True` but `tl.disable_tma_lower=False`, the optimization pipeline skipped the `WarpSpecialized` + `InjectTmaBarrier` passes, leaving TMA load instructions referencing undeclared `mbarrier` symbols. This caused NVCC compilation failure: `identifier \"mbarrier\" is undefined`.\r\n\r\n**Root cause:** `OptimizeForTarget` in `phase.py` gated the entire Hopper pipeline on `allow_tma_and_warp_specialized()`, which required both TMA *and* WS to be enabled. When WS was disabled, the pipeline fell through to the generic branch that lacks barrier allocation/injection.\r\n\r\n**Fix:**\r\n- Add `allow_tma_lower()` that only checks TMA capability, decoupled from warp specialization\r\n- Change the Hopper pipeline entry condition to `allow_tma_lower()` so the `WarpSpecialized` pass (which supports a mbarrier-only mode when WS is disabled) and `InjectTmaBarrier` still run\r\n- Fix `inject_tma_barrier.cc` to promote raw `IntImm` barrier ids to `get_mbarrier()` calls for multi-dimensional (descriptor-based) TMA loads in the degenerate producer-only path\r\n\r\nFixes #737, #1648\r\n\r\n## Test plan\r\n\r\n- [x] `pre-commit run --all-files` passes\r\n- [x] New regression test `test_tilelang_issue_tma_no_ws.py` covers both 1D and 2D-descriptor TMA paths\r\n- [x] Full test suite on H20 (SM90): 784 passed, 107 skipped — all 19 failures are pre-existing NVRTC/cutedsl issues (verified identical on clean `origin/main`)\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **New Features**\n  * TMA lowering can be enabled independently of warp specialization for more flexible compilation paths.\n\n* **Bug Fixes**\n  * Improved barrier insertion and promotion so non-1D and 1D TMA load patterns are handled reliably.\n\n* **Tests**\n  * Added CUDA tests that validate TMA lowering without warp specialization, barrier emission, descriptor usage, and end-to-end kernel execution.\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
